1) Arthur and Mera`s first meeting is in this scene. She doesn`t mention her name and only refers to him as "Atlanna`s first born". It`s pretty straightforward that Mera knew about him before they actually met, as the 2018 movie equally indicates but wasn`t formally presented to him until this event. 

2) The meeting in the 2018 solo movie happens after the Steppenwolf incident, as there is a reference to it from Mera, to convince Arthur to help her again. 

3) This may be Snyder`s take on "Atlantis" (a bunch of old ruins) but even with that sort of aesthetic choice and despite the title in this video, it is clearly no city (of Atlantis). It`s an outpost. Therefore, different directors accounted, there is no plothole regarding Arthur having been to/inside the capital before. 

4) The whole bubble thing and eye color are just aesthetic differences from the directors and can easily fit it, regardless. Arthur`s standard eyes are blue like his mother but yellow when he communicates with sea life and the bubble scene can be explained as Mera not being sure how much Arthur was aware of his own abilities underwater having lived most of his life above the surface, so she played it safe. 

5) The main inconsistency between the two offerings is regarding to what Arthur knew about his mother. In JL he believes she left him and didn`t cared for him whereas in Aquaman, and mostly because his father is part of the story, knows why she left and holds little to no grudges towards her. The other inconsistency would be regarding as to when/where he got the previous trident and armor but that would be simply extrapolated as having been handled by Vulko.
